<div class="home-content">
  <article class="article-about">
    <h3>About Eie.io Garden App</h3>
    <p>Believe it or not Old MacDonald started off in a small backyard garden, this was long before he became
    obsessed with writing songs about animals and farming.  This app was the first app he used "back in the day" to help
    him track, document, manage information about the plants in his garden.</p>
  </article>
  <hr>
  <article class="article-getStarted">
    <h4>How to get started.</h4>
    <p>The Eie.io Garden App allows a user to create and track activities in your backyard
      garden. </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Step 1: Create an Account or Log in.</li>
      <li>Step 2: Create a Garden</li>
      <ul>
        <li>The app will walk you through a series of steps to set up garden sections.</li>
        <li>There are no limts to the number of gardens you can create and track.</li>
        <li>There are no limts to the number of sections you can create and track.</li>
        <li>A section can only have one crop.</li>
      </ul>
      <% if (currentUser) { %>
        <li>The Show Gardens button opens a list of your gardens.</li>
        <ul>
          <li>You can edit, add or delete gardens.</li>
          <li>You can edit, add or delete garden sections.</li>
          <li>You can also modify or delete your account at anytime (however, all data will be lost).</li>
        </ul>
      <% } %>
    </ol>
  </article>

